Soups And Stews, Broccoli, Cheddar, Dinner, Lunch, Appetizer, Main Course|0
Soups And Stews, Broccoli, Cheddar, Dinner, Lunch, Appetizer, Main Course|0
6 tablespoons unsalted butter|1
1 large yellow onion, finely chopped|1
2 cloves garlic, finely chopped|1
Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper|1
2 pounds broccoli, florets with stems peeled and trimmed to 3 inches|1
cup all-purpose flour|1
3 cups low-sodium chicken or vegetable broth|1
2 cups half and half|1
8 ounces very sharp Cheddar, grated, plus more for the top|1
teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg|1
Ingredient Substitution Guide|0
Nutritional Information|0
Note: The information shown is Edamams estimate based on available ingredients and preparation. It should not be considered a substitute for a professional nutritionists advice.|0
Powered by Edamam|0
Reduce heat to low and simmer until liquid has thickened and reduced by about 1/4 and the broccoli is completely tender, 25 to 30 minutes.|0
Season soup with salt and pepper, and divide among bowls. Top with remaining 1 cup broccoli, more Cheddar (if you like), and lots of freshly ground pepper.|0
